Hail Ak'Anon!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 1:08:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2503.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on creation please, esp from Shamans and Enchante</span><hr size=1> The Enchanter is a class with a lot of nuances. You have access to the vast majority of spell effects, in addition to having a huge number of spells per level, so you'll find yourself shifting between spell sets and blowing a large chunk of cash on spells. Combine this with the fact that getting a fair share of the loot may be difficult, depending on the group, and you can expect to be low on cash quite often. You can also expect to be low on mana, as everyone will demand something of you that will make balancing things difficult; once you get Augmentation at 29, the constant expenditure of mana for hastes will be reduced, but the expense of your slows and buffs will more than make up for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Enchanters are primarily a defensive support class, much like a Cleric. Due to the fact that, if you're good, you can turn a deathtrap into an easily winnable situation, you'll rarely lack the opportunity to group. Soloing is more difficult, especially if you don't have an extremely high Charisma, as your primary mechanism for soloing is Charm. You can, of course, use the classic &quot;root-and-nuke&quot; method, but the fact that your direct damage spell line (the *one* direct damage spell line we get <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) is all-or-nothing, easily resistable, and inflicts precious little damage while having a stun component for that extra bit of taunting will make this path difficult. The Animations help, but they're easily destroyed if nothing else is there to help them. This is a function of the fact that an Enchanter's job is to improve the efficiency of the group, not to destroy their foes.<br>
<br>
So, as much as I love playing my Enchanter, I have to admit it's an acquired taste. If you like grouping, don't mind dying (Enchanters and Clerics tend to be the first people to die, mostly because of the aggro levels of their spells and the fact that they're chain-casting them), and have a very high situational awareness, you might like the class. If you want to be the character who stands out in the forefront, taking the enemy down with your magics or melee, a Druid or Shaman would be best of the four classes you mentioned. If you want to be constantly asked into groups, Druids and Clerics are quite popular because of SoW and powerful healing/resurrections, respectively.<br>
<br>
I can offer more advice on enchanting if you want; Illudin is now in the 30th circle of mysteries, and I'm more than happy to answer questions about the class both in and out of character. It's a tricky class to play, but depending on what you want to play, it can be very rewarding. <p>Illudin Arbitrator &lt;Society of Adventurers&gt;<br>
Enchanter and Incorrigible Adventurer<br>
Bringing together and calming Norrathians since 3174<br>
"Onward, all, to our destinies! Adventure awaits!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utimiachaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Timia Chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 7:51:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2503.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks everyone for your comments so far!</span><hr size=1> Much as I think the Enchanter would be the most fun if I had more time to play, I supect I won't be able to play enough to be very effective with it.  Also, my biggest complaint as a Druid was the constant downtime to regen mana, unless I had a breeze or clarity.  I had hoped having constant access to breeze or clarity would solve that with the enchanter, but it sounds like that may not be the case.  Have they done anything else in the last 10 months to reduce mana downtime for casters?<br>
