 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utimiachaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Timia Chaos</A> at: 8/8/02 8:04:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaeleth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaeleth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 9:17:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2503.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks everyone for your comments so far!</span><hr size=1> The exp penalty does not exist anymore, so anyone can group with anyone.  I do suggest being  a Vah Shir shaman, may be a little biased being a Vah Shir myself.  They are a very close knit and family based race.  You can usually find another Vah Shir to group with during your newbie days.  Also shamen are in high demand.  The only downside is the constant &quot;Sow please!&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 10:40:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2503.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well....</span><hr size=1> I have played 5 or 6 shaman (all northmen), the highest has been to a hair from 56, my current one is closing in on 54.<br>
<br>
Also played a druid to 53.  No hands on experience on enchanter class.<br>
<br>
I first started playing Shaman on a server switch.  Played  a ranger up to 47 before kunark, and really enjoyed the utility magic and ability to melee.  Shaman seemed the caster type that best fit my play style.  Like to mix it up a bit, can be self sufficient, but also can make a big impact on a group, or even a raid's success.<br>
<br>
Well it wasn't exactly what I had in mind.. You can melee fairly well up to late 20's after that you are pet dependant in that respect.  I thought it was a Wisdom class.  In reality it is a HP/AC class, more like a melee in that respect than a caster.  Why?  at 24 level shaman get a spell called cannibilize.  With this spell they convert 50 hp into 25 mana.  Essentially you are never out of mana as long as you have hitpoints.  The size of your mana pool (wisdom score) becomes secondary to things like hp's and hitpoint regen (also get regeneration spell at lvl 24).  Many very successful shaman in there 50's have wisdom in the 130's.  they instead wear gear to increase AC (prevent getting hit, leaves more for mana conversion) and hitpoints (more for mana conversion).  <br>
<br>
In groups you will buff a lot.  In raids you will buff even more.  <br>
<br>
The true power of the shaman is in debuffing though.  We get the the best line of slows in the game.  Enchanters are second to us in slows and we are second to them in haste.  At lvl 60 the shaman's best slow is 75%.  Without this some encounters are just impossible.  By slow, I mean that the monster will be doing only 25% of its normal damage output if slowed by a lvl 60 shaman.  We get the malisement line (mages are second to us in this) which is similar to the enchanter tash line, except its resistable until the level 60 version.  We get the cripple line, along with enchanters.<br>
<br>
So, you say.. Enchanters can slow, they can tash and they can cripple, plus they get mana regen.  In these ways shaman and Enchanters are similar, but in one important respect they are not.  Shaman have priest class hitpoints and they have chain class armor.  Enchanter slows cast slower and have longer refreshes.  A resisted slow by an enchanter means a dead enchanter in alot of cases.  <br>
<br>
Shaman is a fairly easy class to play, a fairly difficult class to really excel in.<br>
<br>
Anyways this is just a perspective on the shaman class that people don't figure out until higher levels, you should try and figure out how you see yourself.  Are you a bigger than life metal clad figure (all shaman races are medium to large) who is always in the front of the battle, ripping the will to fight out of the enemies throat by brute force?  Or are you a Robe wearing cultured caster type, using subtlety and guile to do the same?  Play what feels right to you. <br>
<br>
Both types are for control freaks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Its just how you go about gaining that control....<br>
<br>
Best place to go for shaman info....<br>
<br>
